headline: Why Chipotle Stock Hit Is Hitting  a 52-Week Low—and Why There’s Still Hope
summary: Chipotle Mexican Grill  hit a 52-week low on Tuesday as the long-term winner continues to get hit by short-term problems that continue to linger.  There’s nothing wrong with Chipotle’s past performance.  The stock slipped 1.1% to $44.38 on Thursday, a new 52-week low, as shares continues to sell off following last week’s earnings report.
